{
  "texts": [
    "For linking domains, authors extended Apache Atlas to run as a catalog for the data mesh, created Slack channels for communication purposes between data teams, and used Google Forums to request data access.",
    "Moreover, a standard folder organization is followed by all teams.",
    "These inter-domain communication methods are generic and ad-hoc, which limits their usability to support the overall data mesh paradigm and its core principles.Previous work fails to address the data mesh's concerns of governing and bridging decentralized domains.",
    "The proposed solutions in that context focused on communication and information-sharing aspects rather than providing an approach that fits the data mesh paradigm and its principles, such as data as a product.",
    "Consequently, the components of the proposed solutions are not well-integrated cohesively."
  ]
}